article.headline: UNLV 84, Fresno St. 71
article.story: LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Junior guard Rene Rougeau scored a career-high 19 points to lead UNLV to an 84-71 victory over Fresno State on Saturday night. Rougeau was 8-of-11 from the field, 5-of-6 from the free-throw line, and had five rebounds. Joe Darger added 17 points and six rebounds for the Rebels (7-2), and Curtis Terry added 15. Wink Adams had 14 points, which included 5-of-6 from the free-throw line. After the Bulldogs scored the game's first two points, the Rebels scored the next 10. UNLV never trailed again, eventually opening a 23-5 lead, which never got below 13 points the rest of the way. Kevin Bell led Fresno State (5-4) with 17 points. Hector Hernandez had 16 points, while Eddie Miller added 15. The game was played at the Orleans Arena because the Rebels' home court at the Thomas & Mack Arena is hosting the National Rodeo Finals. The Rebels were 12-of-13 from the free-throw line. They were also out-rebounded 41-36. UNLV led 52-25 at halftime. In the half, the Rebels were 20-of-38 (54 percent) from the field, while the Bulldogs were 9-of-30 (30 percent). The Rebels built their biggest lead at 71-42 with 13:04 left in the game.
